> [phr34kzz](#comment_1_166Kgk6LesoTpoTTWciSHeq98UB4mTUcsf): I'd rather use IPFS over this. It's useless. Comparing the number of peers/seeders, IPFS is way more stable and act as a better tool for storage purposes. Technically works exactly like ZeroUP with It's Nowhere but it's Everywhere
&nbsp;
The biggest strength of ZeroNet is the ease of access and its web interface. You can even create a web proxy and give freenet users access to the blockchain.. without them having to download the sites to their computer.. kinda like how Bitcoin users can either open up a new wallet by downloading the entire 80gb blockchain, or simply signing up with an online e-wallet provider.
&nbsp;
The fact is, decentralization will never replace centalization. It has its ups and downs. I'd go as far as to say that the only reason it exists in the first place is because of government censorship. Besides circumventing censorship, I'd say the only use for p2p that I can think of it would be, having the ability to host your own content for free, without paying for web hosting and/or cloud storage, but that's about it.
&nbsp;
So yeah, I'm sticking with Zeronet.. precisely because of its ability to bridge the p2p world and the HTTP world.

